'''SWYP (See What You Print)''' is a [[Printer (computing)|printer]] concept developed by technology product design firm Artefact.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sorrel|first=Charlie|title=Touch-Screen Printer Shows You Exactly What It Will Print|url=https://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/09/touch-screen-printer-shows-you-exactly-what-it-will-print/|accessdate=10/11/2013|newspaper=WIRED|date=2011-09-22}}</ref> The concept was released in 2011. It features simplified interactions and a [[Touchscreen|touch screen]] that shows the user exactly what the print output will be.
== Awards == The SWYP concept was the recipient of two industry awards. It received a [[Karl Ferdinand Braun#SID Karl Ferdinand Braun Prize|Braun Prize]] Silver Award in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Swyp – See What You Print Award|url=http://www.braun.com/global/world-of-braun/braun-prize-2012-winners/swyp-van-engelen-buck-spofford.html|publisher=Braun|accessdate=10/11/2013}}</ref> It also received an IXDA Interaction Award for disruptive [[interaction design]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SWYP: See What You Print|url=http://awards.ixda.org/entry/2013/swyp-see-what-you-print/|publisher=IxDA|accessdate=10/11/2013}}</ref>
