TechChange also partners with international development, humanitarian, and peacebuilding organizations such as USAID, US State Department, World Bank and United Nations Foundation to deliver online educational content.<ref name="swarthmore">{{cite web |url= http://www.swarthmore.edu/news-and-events/nick-martin-04-leads-the-way-for-new-swat-entrepreneurs.xml |title=Nick Martin '04 Leads the Way for New Swat Entrepreneurs |work=Swarthmore College Bulletin |publisher=Swarthmore College |date=January 13, 2013 |accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref> In 2012, TechChange partnered with the mHealth Alliance, a joint program hosted by the [[United Nations Foundation]], to create the first online certificate course in [[mHealth]].<ref name="mHealth">{{cite press release |url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2012/5/prweb9556032.htm |title=mHealth Alliance and TechChange to Offer Online Certificate Course on mHealth |publisher=PRWeb |date=May 30, 2012 |accessdate=July 5, 2012}}</ref><ref name="mHealth watch">{{cite web |url=http://mhealthwatch.com/mhealth-alliance-techchange-partner-to-offer-first-of-its-kind-online-certificate-course-on-mhealth-19095/ |title=mHealth Alliance & TechChange Partner to Offer First of its Kind Online Certificate Course on mHealth |publisher=mHealth Watch |date=May 31, 2012 |accessdate=August 4, 2013}}</ref>
TechChange produces educational animations for international development topics and tools. In April 2013, a TechChange animation on [[M-Pesa]], the popular mobile money transfer program was featured as the [[United States Agency for International Development]] video of the week.<ref name="M-Pesa animation">{{cite web |url=http://blog.usaid.gov/2013/04/video-of-the-week-animating-m-pesa/ |title=Video of the Week: Animating M-PESA |publisher=USAID |date=April 2, 2013 |accessdate=August 4, 2013}}</ref>
TechChange has been featured in a variety of publications for their new approaches to online learning and capacity building including the ''New York Times'', ''PBS NewsHour'', ''The Economist'', Fast Company, ''Chronicle of Higher Education'', ''Stanford Social Innovation Review'', ''The Guardian'', and Dowser.org.<ref name="NYT"/><ref name="PBS">{{cite web |url= https://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/2012/07/post-21.html |title=Civic Startups Introduce New Technology to Government |work=PBS News The Rundown Hour |publisher=PBS |date=July 31, 2012 |accessdate=Aug 4, 2013}}</ref><ref name="economist">{{cite web |url= http://www.economist.com/node/21557706 |title=Technology and Development: Geeks for Good |work=Feast and famine blog |publisher=The Economist |date=June 27, 2012 |accessdate=October 3, 2012}}</ref><ref name="chronicle">{{cite web |url= http://chronicle.com/blogs/profhacker/5-tools-for-building-a-next-generation-hybrid-class-website/33529s |title= 5 Tools for Building a Next-Generation ‘Hybrid’ Class Website |work= Profhacker |publisher= Chronicle of Higher Education |date=May 20, 2011 |accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref><ref name="ssir">{{cite web |url= http://www.ssireview.org/blog/entry/whats_holding_back_mobile_phones_for_education |title= What’s Holding Back Mobile Phones for Education? |work= Stanford Social Innovation Review Blog|publisher= Stanford Social Innovation Review |date=February 11, 2013 |accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref><ref name="guardian">{{cite web |url= https://www.theguardian.com/global-development-professionals-network/2013/feb/26/mobile-education-mobile-phones |title= Youth Unemployment: Can Mobile Technology Improve Employability? |work= Global Development Professionals Network |publisher= The Guardian |date=February 26, 2013 |accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref><ref name="dowser">{{cite web |url= http://dowser.org/whats-next-for-mobile-phones-for-public-health-reflections-from-the-2012-mhealth-summit/ |title= Reflections from the 2012 mHealth Summit for Smarter Public Health |work= Dowser blog |publisher= Dowser.org |date= January 3, 2013 |accessdate= March 2, 2013 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130214024636/http://dowser.org/whats-next-for-mobile-phones-for-public-health-reflections-from-the-2012-mhealth-summit/ |archivedate= February 14, 2013 |df= }}</ref>
